@page "/headings"
<PageTitle>Headings (H1–H6) - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="headings">Headings (H1–H6)</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The H1 through H6 components render semantic heading elements with
                design-system-aware styling.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;H1&gt;Main Title&lt;/H1&gt;
&lt;H2&gt;Section Title&lt;/H2&gt;
&lt;H3&gt;Subsection Title&lt;/H3&gt;
&lt;H4&gt;Sub-subsection&lt;/H4&gt;
&lt;H5&gt;Minor Heading&lt;/H5&gt;
&lt;H6&gt;Smallest Heading&lt;/H6&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="visual-hierarchy">Visual Hierarchy</h2>

            <p>Each heading level decreases in size and visual weight:</p>

            <div style="padding: 16px 0;">
                <h1 style="margin: 8px 0;">H1 — Main Title</h1>
                <h2 style="margin: 8px 0;">H2 — Section Title</h2>
                <h3 style="margin: 8px 0;">H3 — Subsection</h3>
                <h4 style="margin: 8px 0;">H4 — Sub-subsection</h4>
            </div>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="parameters">Parameters</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Style</td><td>string?</td><td>Inline styles.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>ChildContent</td><td>RenderFragment</td><td>Heading text.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="headings-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Headings</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Headings</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, heading components render with their native h1 through h6 HTML
                elements and inherit Bootstrap's typography reboot styles. You can apply
                Bootstrap display heading classes such as display-1 or display-4 through the
                Specialization parameter for larger hero-style headings. Bootstrap also provides
                text color utility classes that can be applied through the Class parameter.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="headings-daisyui">DaisyUI Headings</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Headings</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, heading components render as native h1 through h6 elements and
                receive their visual styling from DaisyUI's typography base styles. DaisyUI
                applies consistent font sizing and weight across headings through its base
                CSS layer. The text color adapts to the active DaisyUI theme automatically.
                You can apply additional Tailwind text utility classes through the Class parameter.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="headings-basecoat">Basecoat Headings</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Headings</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, heading components render as native h1 through h6 elements styled
                with Tailwind typography utilities from Basecoat's base configuration. Font size,
                weight, and line height scale from h1 down to h6 following Basecoat's typographic
                scale. You can override or extend heading styles by passing additional Tailwind
                text size or font weight utilities through the Class or Specialization parameters.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("headings", "Headings (H1–H6)"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("visual-hierarchy", "Visual Hierarchy", 2),
    new TocItem("parameters", "Parameters", 2),
    new TocItem("headings-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Headings", 2),
    new TocItem("headings-daisyui", "DaisyUI Headings", 2),
    new TocItem("headings-basecoat", "Basecoat Headings", 2)
])" />

</div>
